The paper proposes a measurement-based voltage stability assessment framework using online deep learning. This involves the use of gradient-based adaptive learning algorithms and the modification of the proximal function adaptively. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category covers papers that focus on the development of machine learning algorithms and techniques. The paper proposes an online deep learning approach for voltage stability assessment, which falls under this sub-category. 

- cs.SY (Systems and Control): This sub-category covers papers that focus on the design and analysis of control systems. The paper proposes a framework for voltage stability assessment, which involves the use of adaptive learning algorithms. This falls under the scope of this sub-category. 

- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers papers that focus on the development of artificial intelligence algorithms and techniques. The paper proposes an online deep learning approach for voltage stability assessment, which falls under this sub-category. 

- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): This sub-category covers papers that focus on the development of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms.
